Red Cross worker Rene Schulthoff photographed girl in Jordanian refugee camp . 
  She mistook his camera for a weapon and raised her arms to surrender in November . 
  He did not realise how terrified she was until he was editing the photographs . 
  Follows iconic image of four-year-old Adi Hudea who also surrendered to camera in Syrian camp . 
  Around 17,000 Syrians have fled to Jordan after fleeing war in Syria . 
  War Child says children 'grow up in permanent fear and under poor conditions'